Financeasy is a Java-based program which takes your monthly budget and calculates based on your financial necessities how to spend your money. 
There's an area with stores with different products, you can find the cheapest store, the closest one and you can search for a specific product and where it's cheapest. 
Then it calculates depending on your needs the most optimal store you can shop at.
The source code mainly uses a hierarchy of classes with "Products" being the parent abstract class.
The method for calculating the money-spend-ratio is in "Budget".
